window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>What happens when a troll gets trolled?</b></p> <p>Chad has always been a quick-witted troll. But after an angry outburst during a televised stream, he faces thirty days of full-immersion therapy in a virtual world.</p> <p>At first, it seems like a dream come true—a chance to experience cutting-edge technology and escape into a world of high fantasy. But when he’s forced to play as a forest troll, one of the most-hated monsters in <i>Isle of Mythos</i>, it doesn’t feel much like a game anymore.</p> <p>To make matters worse, the heroes sent to rid the world of evil aren't heroes at all—they're convicted felons on their own twisted paths to redemption.</p> <p>With a target on his back, Chad must learn to harness his rage if he wants to survive in a world where anything goes.</p>"; 
